/*=====================================================
1. OPERATING SYSTEM (OS)
=====================================================*/

Operating System (OS):
OS ek system software hai jo USER aur COMPUTER HARDWARE ke beech interface ka kaam karta hai.

Example:
User â†’ OS â†’ Hardware (CPU, RAM, Disk)

/* Functions of OS */
- Process Management
- Memory Management
- File Management
- Device Management
- Security & Protection


/*=====================================================
2. TYPES OF OPERATING SYSTEM
=====================================================*/

Batch OS:
- Similar jobs ko batch me execute karta
- No user interaction
Example: Payroll system

Time Sharing OS:
- Multiple users ek sath kaam karte
- CPU time slice me divide
Example: Linux, Windows

Distributed OS:
- Multiple computers ek system jaise kaam
Example: Google servers

Real Time OS (RTOS):
- Time critical systems
Example: Missile system, Medical devices


/*=====================================================
3. MULTIPROGRAMMING vs MULTITASKING
=====================================================*/

Multiprogramming:
- Multiple programs memory me load
- CPU idle na rahe
Example: Server systems

Multitasking:
- Single user multiple tasks run
Example: Chrome + Music + VS Code


/*=====================================================
4. KERNEL MODE & USER MODE
=====================================================*/

User Mode:
- Limited access
- Direct hardware access nahi

Kernel Mode:
- Full access
- OS yahi run hota

System Call:
User Mode â†’ Kernel Mode

Example:
read(), write(), fork()


/*=====================================================
5. PROCESS
=====================================================*/

Process:
Program jo execution me hai

Process States:
- New
- Ready
- Running
- Waiting
- Terminated

Example:
.c file â†’ compile â†’ program â†’ execution = process


/*=====================================================
6. FUNCTION CALL vs SYSTEM CALL
=====================================================*/

Function Call:
- User space
- Fast
Example: printf()

System Call:
- Kernel space
- OS service
Example: read(), write()


/=====================================================
PROCESS MANAGEMENT
=====================================================*/

/*=====================================================
7. STARVATION & AGING
=====================================================*/

Starvation:
- Low priority process ko CPU na milna

Aging:
- Time ke sath priority increase
- Starvation avoid karta


/*=====================================================
8. PROCESS SYNCHRONIZATION
=====================================================*/

Synchronization:
- Shared data ko safe rakhna

Problem:
Race Condition

Tools:
- Mutex
- Semaphore
- Monitor


/*=====================================================
9. SEMAPHORE
=====================================================*/

Semaphore:
- Integer variable
- Synchronization ke liye

Types:
Binary Semaphore:
- 0 or 1
- Mutex jaisa

Counting Semaphore:
- Any integer
- Multiple resources handle


/*=====================================================
10. DEADLOCK
=====================================================*/

Deadlock:
Processes ek dusre ke resources ka wait kare

Deadlock Conditions:
1. Mutual Exclusion
2. Hold & Wait
3. No Preemption
4. Circular Wait


/* Deadlock Prevention */
- Mutual exclusion avoid
- Preemption allow
- Resources order fix


/*=====================================================
11. BANKER'S ALGORITHM
=====================================================*/

Bankerâ€™s Algorithm:
- Deadlock avoidance algorithm
- Safe state check karta

Example:
Bank loan dene se pehle check karta
safe hai ya nahi


/=====================================================
MEMORY MANAGEMENT
=====================================================*/

/*=====================================================
12. MEMORY MANAGEMENT TECHNIQUES
=====================================================*/

First Fit:
- Pehli sufficient block allocate

Best Fit:
- Sabse chhoti suitable block

Worst Fit:
- Sabse badi block allocate


/*=====================================================
13. VIRTUAL MEMORY
=====================================================*/

Virtual Memory:
- Disk ko RAM jaisa use
- Large programs run kar sakte

Example:
Paging system


/*=====================================================
14. DYNAMIC BINDING
=====================================================*/

Dynamic Binding:
- Address runtime par decide
- Flexibility zyada

Static Binding:
- Compile time address fix


/*=====================================================
15. PAGE FAULT
=====================================================*/

Page Fault:
- Required page RAM me nahi
- Disk se load hoti

Valid Page Fault:
- Page disk me present

Invalid Page Fault:
- Illegal access â†’ crash


/*=====================================================
16. BELADY'S ANOMALY
=====================================================*/

Beladyâ€™s Anomaly:
- Frames badhane par page faults badh jate

Occurs in:
- FIFO algorithm

Does NOT occur in:
- LRU
- Optimal


/*=====================================================
17. THRASHING
=====================================================*/

Thrashing:
- CPU low usage
- Paging zyada
- System slow

Solution:
- Working set model
- Increase RAM


/*=====================================================
18. CACHE
=====================================================*/

Cache:
- Fast memory
- CPU aur RAM ke beech

Purpose:
- Access time reduce


/*=====================================================
19. CACHE MAPPING
=====================================================*/

Direct Mapping:
- One block â†’ one cache line

Associative Mapping:
- Any block â†’ any cache line


/=====================================================
FILE SYSTEM
=====================================================*/

/*=====================================================
20. FILE SYSTEM
=====================================================*/

File System:
- Files ko store & manage karta

Components:
- Files
- Directories
- Metadata


/*=====================================================
21. TYPES OF FILE SYSTEM
=====================================================*/

FAT
NTFS
EXT3
EXT4


/*=====================================================
22. FILE ALLOCATION
=====================================================*/

Contiguous Allocation:
- Continuous blocks

Linked Allocation:
- Pointer based

Indexed Allocation:
- Index block use


/*=====================================================
23. FRAGMENTATION
=====================================================*/

Internal Fragmentation:
- Memory waste inside block

External Fragmentation:
- Free space scattered


/=====================================================
I/O SYSTEM
=====================================================*/

/*=====================================================
24. BLOCKING vs NON-BLOCKING
=====================================================*/

Blocking:
- Process wait karta

Non-Blocking:
- Process continue karta


/*=====================================================
25. SYNCHRONOUS vs ASYNCHRONOUS
=====================================================*/

Synchronous:
- Step by step execution

Asynchronous:
- Parallel execution


/*=====================================================
26. SPOOLING
=====================================================*/

Spooling:
- I/O ko disk me store
- Sequential execution

Example:
Printer queue


/=====================================================
STORAGE MANAGEMENT & SECURITY
=====================================================*/

/*=====================================================
27. SECURITY THREATS & VULNERABILITIES
=====================================================*/

Threats:
- Virus
- Worm
- Trojan
- Phishing

Vulnerabilities:
- Weak password
- Unpatched software


