/*=====================================================
1. INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER NETWORKS
=====================================================*/

Computer Network:
Do ya do se zyada computers ka group jo data share kare.

Example:
Internet, Office LAN


Types of Network:
LAN â€“ Local Area Network (Office, Home)
MAN â€“ Metropolitan Area Network (City)
WAN â€“ Wide Area Network (Internet)


Hub vs Switch vs Router:
Hub:
- Broadcast device
- No intelligence

Switch:
- MAC address use
- Fast

Router:
- IP address use
- Internet connect karta


Network Topology:
Bus, Star, Ring, Mesh

Most used:
Star topology (easy + fast)


Nodes & Links:
Node = device
Link = connection


/=====================================================
2. OSI MODEL
=====================================================*/

OSI Model:
7-layer reference model for networking

Layers (Top â†’ Bottom):
7 Application
6 Presentation
5 Session
4 Transport
3 Network
2 Data Link
1 Physical

Interview Trick:
"All People Seem To Need Data Processing"


/=====================================================
3. TCP/IP MODEL
=====================================================*/

TCP/IP Model:
Practical model used in real networks

Layers:
- Application
- Transport
- Internet
- Network Access


OSI vs TCP/IP:
OSI = theoretical
TCP/IP = practical


/=====================================================
PHYSICAL LAYER
=====================================================*/

Data Transmission:
- Simplex
- Half Duplex
- Full Duplex


Bandwidth:
Data transfer capacity
Unit: bps


Transmission Media:
Wired:
- Twisted Pair
- Coaxial
- Optical Fiber

Wireless:
- Radio
- Microwave
- Infrared


/=====================================================
DATA LINK LAYER
=====================================================*/

Data Link Layer:
- Node to node delivery
- Error control

Functions:
- Framing
- Error detection
- Flow control


Error Detection:
- Parity bit
- CRC
- Checksum


Data Link Protocols:
- HDLC
- PPP


Multiple Access Protocols:
- ALOHA
- CSMA/CD
- CSMA/CA


MAC Address:
- 48-bit address
- Unique
- Assigned by manufacturer


Channel Allocation Problem:
- Multiple users ek channel share kare
Solution:
TDMA, FDMA


Data Link Switching:
Switch MAC table use karta


Ethernet LAN:
Most popular LAN technology


/=====================================================
NETWORK LAYER
=====================================================*/

Network Layer:
- Source to destination delivery
- Routing

IP Addressing:
IPv4 â€“ 32 bit
IPv6 â€“ 128 bit


Subnetting:
IP ko parts me divide
Purpose:
- Efficient IP usage
- Security


ICMP:
Error reporting protocol
Example:
Ping command


Fragmentation:
Large packet â†’ small fragments


Tunneling:
Ek protocol ke andar dusra


Gateway vs Router:
Router:
Same network

Gateway:
Different networks


Count to Infinity Problem:
Routing loop problem
Solution:
Split horizon, poison reverse


/=====================================================
TRANSPORT LAYER
=====================================================*/

Transport Layer:
End to end communication


Elements:
- Segmentation
- Error control
- Flow control


TCP:
- Connection oriented
- Reliable
- Slow

Example:
HTTP, FTP


UDP:
- Connectionless
- Fast
- Unreliable

Example:
Video streaming, Gaming


TCP State Transition:
CLOSED â†’ LISTEN â†’ SYN â†’ ESTABLISHED â†’ FIN


3-Way Handshaking:
1. SYN
2. SYN-ACK
3. ACK


Congestion Control:
- Slow Start
- Congestion Avoidance
- Fast Retransmit


/=====================================================
SESSION LAYER
=====================================================*/

Session Layer:
- Session establish
- Session maintain
- Session terminate


/=====================================================
PRESENTATION LAYER
=====================================================*/

Presentation Layer:
- Data format
- Encryption
- Compression


/=====================================================
APPLICATION LAYER
=====================================================*/

DNS:
Domain name â†’ IP address

Example:
google.com â†’ IP


WWW:
Web services using HTTP


HTTP:
Stateless protocol
Port: 80


FTP:
File transfer protocol
Port: 21


SMTP:
Email send protocol
Port: 25


DHCP:
Automatic IP assign karta


/=====================================================
NETWORK SECURITY
=====================================================*/

Network Security:
Data ko protect karna


Cryptography:
Data encryption technique


Encryption Types:
Symmetric:
DES, AES

Asymmetric:
RSA, Diffie-Hellman


Hash Function:
Fixed size output
Example:
SHA-256


Digital Signature:
Authentication + Integrity


Security Protocols:
SSL, TLS, HTTPS


VPN:
Secure private network


Network Attacks:
- DoS
- Man-in-the-middle
- Phishing


/=====================================================
NETWORK TROUBLESHOOTING
=====================================================*/

Ping Command:
Check connectivity


Delay Types:
- Processing delay
- Queuing delay
- Transmission delay
- Propagation delay


